summary:
Iteration 3 final verification for Gemini -> Gemma 4 rename on /architecture page. Initial DOM check across all 7 pages returned 0 gemini occurrences, but /architecture had a hidden compile-error overlay (dev CRA overlay was above document.body, so page.innerText was empty). Root cause: leftover duplicate/malformed lines 125-128 in Architecture.jsx after the previous edit ('">{body}</pre>
    </div>
  );
}' orphan block) causing 'Unterminated string constant (125:0)' SyntaxError. Removed the leftover garbage. After the fix, all 7 pages render cleanly and /architecture displays 11 correct 'Gemma 4' references and 0 'Gemini' references.

rca of the issue:
During the previous rename patch, a duplicate fragment '">{body}</pre>
    </div>
  );
}' was appended after the CodeCard function's true closing brace at line 124. Babel raised 'Unterminated string constant. (125:0)' and CRA displayed the compile-error overlay, making /architecture render nothing (page.innerText was empty, which caused the initial gemini==0 false-positive). Mitigation: deleted lines 125-128. Reproduction: git-checkout the pre-fix Architecture.jsx and load /architecture — the CRA red overlay 'Module build failed / SyntaxError' will appear.
